step_data.thought:
Looking at the current page state, I can see that I've already clicked the 'Zoom In' button four times, progressively increasing the zoom level. The URL now shows '#map=13/42.8960/-75.1080' where '13' is the current zoom level (up from the initial level which appears to have been 10).

The image URLs in the accessibility tree confirm we're now at zoom level 13, with tiles like 'https://tile.openstreetmap.org/13/2386/3013.png'.

The 'Zoom In' link (bid 406) is still available and focused. To see even more detailed road information, I'll click this button one more time to further increase the zoom level to 14. This should reveal even more detailed road features, potentially showing smaller streets, paths, and more precise road labels.

Each zoom level approximately doubles the detail level, so going from level 13 to 14 will provide significantly more road detail, which aligns with the user's goal.
